WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:34.826 --> 00:00:39.456
We must begin our story. sad to say.
with an empty chair.

3
00:00:40.582 --> 00:00:44.086
If it were not empty.
we would not have a story.

4
00:00:44.336 --> 00:00:49.132
But it is. and we do. and
it is time to tell it.

5
00:01:13.448 --> 00:01:15.868
This is the story of my family.

6
00:01:16.118 --> 00:01:19.204
of my seven children.
who are all very clever

7
00:01:19.454 --> 00:01:23.166
but all very. very. very naughty.

8
00:01:28.505 --> 00:01:30.549
This is Nanny Whetstone.

9
00:01:30.799 --> 00:01:33.886
the 17th nanny I had hired
to look after my children.

10
00:01:34.136 --> 00:01:37.097
She was the strictest. the toughest

11
00:01:37.347 --> 00:01:40.934
and the most fearless
nanny in all the land.

12
00:01:42.936 --> 00:01:45.856
As I went to work that day
at the funeral parlour.

13
00:01:46.106 --> 00:01:48.567
I was confident in the knowledge...

14
00:01:48.692 --> 00:01:51.653
that there was nothing.
absolutely nothing

15
00:01:51.904 --> 00:01:55.866
that my children could do to upset her.

16
00:01:56.116 --> 00:01:58.118
They've eaten the baby!

17
00:01:59.203 --> 00:02:00.662
Except that.

18
00:02:14.968 --> 00:02:17.387
- Quick! He's coming!
- Hide!

19
00:02:17.638 --> 00:02:19.598
- Quiet!
- Stop it!

20
00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:39.910
Children. where's Aggy?

21
00:02:55.759 --> 00:02:57.302
Look at you.

22
00:02:57.553 --> 00:02:59.596
You're all cabbagey.

23
00:02:59.847 --> 00:03:03.392
Oh...and you're all gravy-y.

24
00:03:03.642 --> 00:03:08.313
As was your intention. Nanny Whetstone
has resigned from her post.

25
00:03:08.564 --> 00:03:12.359
I shall go to the agency this afternoon
and hire a new nanny.

26
00:03:12.609 --> 00:03:17.155
You will not drive her away
as you have done with her predecessors.

27
00:03:20.576 --> 00:03:21.535
Papa.

28
00:03:22.452 --> 00:03:24.872
Can't catch me out.
That showed 'em who's boss.

29
00:03:29.293 --> 00:03:32.421
Three days. eight hours and 47 minutes.

30
00:03:32.671 --> 00:03:34.882
So that got rid of her...

31
00:03:35.132 --> 00:03:37.968
23 hours and 13 minutes
quicker than the last one.

32
00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:42.723
I think the turning point was definitely
eating the baby. Well done. Eric.

33
00:03:43.849 --> 00:03:46.643
Mr Brown. are you all right?

34
00:03:46.894 --> 00:03:48.729
I'm perfectly all right.

35
00:03:48.979 --> 00:03:54.318
Evangeline. could you let Cook know
that the new nanny has had to leave

36
00:03:54.526 --> 00:03:57.529
and I'm off to the agency
to find a new one?

37
00:04:05.037 --> 00:04:08.123
Good. I'll just...

38
00:04:22.513 --> 00:04:25.307
- Mrs Partridge?
- We're closed.

39
00:04:25.557 --> 00:04:27.851
- There's been a tiny hiccup.
- We're not here.

40
00:04:28.101 --> 00:04:30.395
- Please. let me in...
- Go away.

41
00:04:30.646 --> 00:04:34.066
Listen. they didn't eat the baby.
It was a chicken. actually.

42
00:04:34.316 --> 00:04:37.861
There's no more nannies!
You've had your lot.

43
00:04:47.204 --> 00:04:51.124
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

44
00:04:51.375 --> 00:04:53.627
Is that you. Mrs Partridge?

45
00:04:54.670 --> 00:04:59.508
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

46
00:04:59.758 --> 00:05:03.428
I need her to start right away.
I'm late for a vital tea dance.

47
00:05:03.679 --> 00:05:06.348
Nanny McPhee is not on our books.

48
00:05:06.598 --> 00:05:10.435
Nanny McPhee is not on anyone's books.

49
00:05:12.521 --> 00:05:14.231
Nanny Whetstone's gone.

50
00:05:14.481 --> 00:05:18.569
There's a surprise.
Hurry it up there. Spuds.

51
00:05:18.819 --> 00:05:23.782
Mr Brown's gone to the agency.
I said the children'll be fine with us.

52
00:05:24.032 --> 00:05:26.076
They won't be fine with me.

53
00:05:26.285 --> 00:05:29.580
I won't have them dirty blighters
in my kitchen. and that is that!

54
00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:33.500
I have it in writing. In writing!

55
00:05:37.171 --> 00:05:40.591
- Well. that's the final straw.
- Pa!

56
00:05:40.841 --> 00:05:42.885
There are no more nannies.

57
00:05:43.135 --> 00:05:46.430
None. All over. finished.

58
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:49.933
I've had to cancel my appointment
and that will cause trouble.

59
00:05:50.184 --> 00:05:55.147
- I told them not to. It wasn't my idea.
- Don't look at me! It's not my fault.

60
00:05:55.397 --> 00:05:58.192
Well. you seem intent
on distressing me...

61
00:05:58.442 --> 00:06:01.653
Er...don't do that. darling. please.
That's my sore bit.

62
00:06:03.322 --> 00:06:06.450
You seem intent on distressing me.
so I'm going to distress you.

63
00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:10.579
You are to...to go to bed immediately.

64
00:06:10.829 --> 00:06:13.498
Before supper?

65
00:06:16.084 --> 00:06:18.170
Without supper.

66
00:06:19.379 --> 00:06:22.049
Did he say without supper?

67
00:06:22.257 --> 00:06:24.676
Never mind that.

68
00:06:24.927 --> 00:06:28.305
There's no more nannies.

69
00:06:28.555 --> 00:06:31.767
Poor him...and poor them.

70
00:06:32.017 --> 00:06:34.353
Poor them. my Aunt Fanny.

71
00:06:34.603 --> 00:06:37.356
They're the worstest.
nastiest. horriblest...

72
00:06:37.606 --> 00:06:40.859
It'll be snow in August
before this family's straightened out.

73
00:06:41.109 --> 00:06:45.113
"Dear Nanny Whetstone.
I'm so very sorry."

74
00:06:45.364 --> 00:06:47.783
"My children..."

75
00:06:48.033 --> 00:06:51.245
Eric. give it back to her!
Give it back now! Stop it!

76
00:06:51.495 --> 00:06:52.996
My children.

77
00:06:55.624 --> 00:06:58.585
Eric! Eric. that's my teddy!

78
00:06:58.836 --> 00:07:02.047
- Eric. stop doing this!
- Give it back!

79
00:07:04.049 --> 00:07:07.219
- Stop fighting!
- Oi. you lot!

80
00:07:07.469 --> 00:07:10.305
Quiet!

81
00:07:10.556 --> 00:07:15.143
You're driving your poor father
to distraction. Stop it.

82
00:07:16.270 --> 00:07:19.606
Lily. what's this word?

83
00:07:19.857 --> 00:07:23.318
Lovingly."He took her
lovingly by the hand."

84
00:07:23.569 --> 00:07:25.112
What's your book about. Evangeline?

85
00:07:25.362 --> 00:07:29.575
It's about the daughter of a nice man
who remarries after his wife dies

86
00:07:29.825 --> 00:07:31.577
and the stepmother's horrid to her.

87
00:07:31.827 --> 00:07:34.204
Why doesn't the man
stop her being horrid?

88
00:07:34.454 --> 00:07:37.374
Fathers all turn bad
once their wives die.

89
00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:39.168
They don't care any more.

90
00:07:39.418 --> 00:07:42.629
Simon. Yours does.

91
00:07:42.880 --> 00:07:44.590
No. he doesn't.

92
00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:49.761
Does he read to Chrissie
or play cricket with us like he used to?

93
00:07:50.012 --> 00:07:53.307
He doesn't even sing Loola-bye to Aggy.
We hardly see him.

94
00:07:53.557 --> 00:07:58.520
He loves you. Simon. You know that.
He's just had a lot on his mind since...

95
00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:01.148
Since Mother died.

96
00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:10.490
You used to be as close as anything.

97
00:08:10.741 --> 00:08:15.579
Not any more. All he cares about now
is getting himself a nice new wife.

98
00:08:18.081 --> 00:08:22.085
Well... I don't know
if that's true or not.

99
00:08:22.336 --> 00:08:24.713
but it might be nice
to have a new mother.

100
00:08:24.963 --> 00:08:27.883
Don't you know anything about the world?

101
00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:31.595
Whoever he marries will be vile
and treat us like slaves.

102
00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:35.390
- You don't know that.
- Plenty of hard evidence for it.

103
00:08:35.641 --> 00:08:40.604
There isn't one stepmother in there
who's even halfway decent.

104
00:08:40.854 --> 00:08:45.526
They're an evil breed. Anyway.
who ever likes other people's children?

105
00:08:45.776 --> 00:08:47.528
I like you.

106
00:08:47.778 --> 00:08:51.073
Yes. but you're a servant.
You're paid to like us.

107
00:08:51.323 --> 00:08:53.325
That doesn't count.

108
00:08:56.703 --> 00:08:59.957
I've got my work to be getting on with.

109
00:09:03.377 --> 00:09:05.379
I really am hungry. Evangeline.

110
00:09:05.629 --> 00:09:09.508
Could you maybe bring me
some secret toast and jam?

111
00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:13.095
All right. forget the jam.
Just some secret toast.

112
00:09:23.856 --> 00:09:26.984
Shall I plump the cushion
on Mrs Brown's chair?

113
00:09:27.234 --> 00:09:29.820
I know you like to plump it yourself
sometimes.

114
00:09:30.070 --> 00:09:34.116
Oh. no. that's...that's all right.
You plump away. Evangeline. Thank you.

115
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:44.960
I was wondering if I might make
Master Sebastian a piece of toast.

116
00:09:45.210 --> 00:09:48.422
Yes. I should think...
Er...no. under no circumstances. No.

117
00:09:48.630 --> 00:09:50.507
I could do it secret-like.

118
00:09:50.716 --> 00:09:54.303
No. they'll hear him chewing
and then we're done for.

119
00:09:55.512 --> 00:09:57.014
No. they get nothing.

120
00:09:57.222 --> 00:09:59.057
Righto. Mr Brown.

121
00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:05.856
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

122
00:10:08.066 --> 00:10:09.818
Nanny McPhee.

123
00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:21.079
No supper.

124
00:10:21.330 --> 00:10:24.499
Discipline. That's more like it.

125
00:10:49.733 --> 00:10:53.195
Now. you listen here.
you pustular tykes.

126
00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:56.490
You ain't allowed in this kitchen.
not now. not ever.

127
00:10:56.740 --> 00:10:58.408
I have it in writing.

128
00:10:59.743 --> 00:11:03.830
Well. dear. the agency
has closed its doors.

129
00:11:04.081 --> 00:11:07.334
What am I to do? Aunt Adelaide says...

130
00:11:07.584 --> 00:11:09.795
Your children are out
of control. Cedric.

131
00:11:10.045 --> 00:11:12.256
And there was that thing she said...

132
00:11:12.339 --> 00:11:15.050
about their needing a
female influence. I...

133
00:11:16.176 --> 00:11:18.887
You know what she's like.
She'll stop the allowance

134
00:11:19.137 --> 00:11:24.101
unless I marry again and give them
a new mother within the month.

135
00:11:24.351 --> 00:11:29.606
A month. I mean. it's unbearable.
But l... I had to... I had to promise.

136
00:11:32.150 --> 00:11:37.239
Remember we talked about
what would happen without her money.

137
00:11:37.489 --> 00:11:39.783
The bank will take the house.

138
00:11:40.033 --> 00:11:44.246
There'll be debtors' prison for me.
workhouse for the older children.

139
00:11:44.496 --> 00:11:47.666
Goodness only knows
what'll happen to little Chrissie.

140
00:11:47.916 --> 00:11:50.002
And as for Aggy...

141
00:11:50.252 --> 00:11:52.546
it's unimaginable.

142
00:12:00.179 --> 00:12:04.183
Where are you? You mewling half-bakes!

143
00:12:04.433 --> 00:12:06.935
I'm ready for you. And I'm hard!

144
00:12:14.735 --> 00:12:16.737
This is fun!

145
00:12:17.905 --> 00:12:19.239
We got Cook!

146
00:12:19.489 --> 00:12:23.911
The person you need is Nanny McPhee.

147
00:12:24.161 --> 00:12:26.997
Jump!

148
00:12:27.247 --> 00:12:30.000
Eric. you're not making another bomb.
are you?

149
00:12:32.628 --> 00:12:35.839
McPhee...

150
00:12:36.089 --> 00:12:38.258
Jump!

151
00:12:38.509 --> 00:12:40.844
- Oh!
- Jump!

152
00:12:43.180 --> 00:12:48.519
- They're in the kitchen.
- No! No! You took them down for toast!

153
00:12:48.769 --> 00:12:51.563
I never did!
You sent them to bed with no dinner.

154
00:12:51.813 --> 00:12:53.190
- That's what done it!
- Don't tell...

155
00:13:02.991 --> 00:13:04.493
- I'll. er...
- Why don't you...?

156
00:13:04.743 --> 00:13:06.370
- I'll go.
- No. I'd better...

157
00:13:06.620 --> 00:13:09.414
- Well. no. I can...
- You. erm... I'll...

158
00:13:09.665 --> 00:13:13.460
- I'll be off. then.
- Yes. you... I'll just...

159
00:13:43.740 --> 00:13:47.619
Good evening. Mr Brown.
I am Nanny McPhee.

160
00:13:49.162 --> 00:13:52.374
Oh. you're... Er...of course.

161
00:13:52.624 --> 00:13:54.877
Good heavens. I suppose the agency...

162
00:13:55.127 --> 00:13:59.464
I do not belong to any agency. Mr Brown.
I am a government nanny.

163
00:13:59.715 --> 00:14:02.509
A government nanny? How...

164
00:14:04.052 --> 00:14:05.220
.. unusual.

165
00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:07.055
May I come in?

166
00:14:07.306 --> 00:14:10.642
Yes. by all means. do...do come in.

167
00:14:15.105 --> 00:14:19.234
I understand you have
extremely ill-behaved children.

168
00:14:19.484 --> 00:14:23.280
No. No. no. No.
No... Good grief. what a suggestion.

169
00:14:25.949 --> 00:14:27.951
- Playful.
- Shut up!

170
00:14:28.202 --> 00:14:30.120
What are your main concerns?

171
00:14:30.370 --> 00:14:31.496
Concerns?

172
00:14:31.747 --> 00:14:34.541
Mm. Do they go to bed when they're told?

173
00:14:34.791 --> 00:14:37.211
Well. no. not. er... No.

174
00:14:37.461 --> 00:14:41.465
- Do they get up when they're told?
- Er...well. no. not exactly.

175
00:14:41.715 --> 00:14:45.302
- Get dressed when they're told?
- Now. that's a good question.

176
00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:50.390
- Do they say "please" and "thank you"?
- In what context?

177
00:14:50.641 --> 00:14:54.102
That will do to be going on with.

178
00:14:54.353 --> 00:14:58.190
Your children need me.

179
00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:02.236
I'll go and make sure everything's
in order before I introduce you.

180
00:15:02.486 --> 00:15:05.280
I shall introduce myself.

181
00:15:05.531 --> 00:15:08.909
Please. Mr Brown.
go back to your newspaper.

182
00:15:30.597 --> 00:15:32.140
Oh. look.

183
00:15:34.351 --> 00:15:37.020
The door's open and
there's nobody there.

184
00:15:40.440 --> 00:15:42.401
I am here.

185
00:15:42.651 --> 00:15:45.028
I am Nanny McPhee.

186
00:15:45.279 --> 00:15:47.948
Oh. did...did somebody speak?

187
00:15:48.156 --> 00:15:52.202
- I didn't hear anything.
- That's because nobody's there.

188
00:15:55.372 --> 00:15:58.792
Then listen carefully
and try to hear this.

189
00:15:59.042 --> 00:16:02.296
Stop what you are doing.
put the kitchen to rights

190
00:16:02.546 --> 00:16:04.298
and go upstairs to bed.

191
00:16:08.177 --> 00:16:11.930
- Did you hear what I said?
- I've just had an idea.

192
00:16:12.181 --> 00:16:16.560
Why don't we play here
in the kitchen all night long?

193
00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:19.021
Let's. let's!

194
00:16:21.607 --> 00:16:25.402
- Excellent notion.
- Tomatoes!

195
00:16:25.652 --> 00:16:29.281
Jump! Jump. jump! Jump!

196
00:16:29.531 --> 00:16:33.285
Jump. jump. jump. jump!

197
00:16:33.535 --> 00:16:36.371
Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump!

198
00:16:36.622 --> 00:16:38.916
Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump!

199
00:16:39.166 --> 00:16:42.085
Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump! Jump...jump...

200
00:16:42.336 --> 00:16:45.047
jump.

201
00:17:02.689 --> 00:17:04.441
Government nanny?

202
00:17:07.736 --> 00:17:08.946
What's she done?

203
00:17:09.196 --> 00:17:13.242
- She's done something to us!
- They went in the pot!

204
00:17:13.492 --> 00:17:14.952
I can't stop!

205
00:17:15.202 --> 00:17:16.745
She banged her stick!

206
00:17:16.995 --> 00:17:18.956
I'm going to be sick!

207
00:17:23.752 --> 00:17:27.214
- It must be magic!
- What's happening?

208
00:17:31.677 --> 00:17:34.179
- Please. Simon. let's stop!
- We've got to stop!

209
00:17:34.429 --> 00:17:36.974
- Let's stop!
- Let's stop!

210
00:17:40.519 --> 00:17:43.188
- Well. stop if you want. then!
- We can't!

211
00:17:43.438 --> 00:17:44.648
It's her fault!

212
00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:46.733
It started when she banged the stick!

213
00:17:46.984 --> 00:17:50.529
- I can't stop!
- Slow down!

214
00:17:51.196 --> 00:17:52.573
Simon!

215
00:17:52.823 --> 00:17:56.285
Come on. whoever you are!
Let's stop this and go to bed!

216
00:17:58.245 --> 00:18:01.039
- Say "please".
- I never say "please".

217
00:18:01.290 --> 00:18:02.332
Very well.

218
00:18:02.583 --> 00:18:04.918
- Please!
- Please!

219
00:18:05.169 --> 00:18:07.921
- Don't touch Aggy!
- Wait!

220
00:18:08.130 --> 00:18:09.840
Say it!

221
00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:13.260
Actually. Simon. would you.
because this baby's gonna blow!

222
00:18:13.510 --> 00:18:17.472
- And Aggy's gonna go in the stockpot!
- Put her back. Chrissie!

223
00:18:18.807 --> 00:18:21.185
Oh. for goodness' sake! Please. then!

224
00:18:23.770 --> 00:18:26.857
Take Aggy off me!

225
00:18:27.107 --> 00:18:29.985
Please. Nanny McPhee.

226
00:18:32.029 --> 00:18:33.405
Chrissie. don't!

227
00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:37.951
- Say it!
- Take Aggy out!

228
00:18:38.202 --> 00:18:40.871
- No. Lily!
- Say it!

229
00:18:41.121 --> 00:18:42.789
Simon!

230
00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:46.793
I can't stop myself!

231
00:18:47.044 --> 00:18:49.421
Please. Nanny McPhee.

232
00:18:50.380 --> 00:18:52.716
I'm going to jump!

233
00:18:52.966 --> 00:18:54.301
Too late!

234
00:19:08.941 --> 00:19:11.068
Blimey.

235
00:19:11.318 --> 00:19:13.403
Up to bed. please.

236
00:19:26.333 --> 00:19:29.586
Goodnight. Mrs Blatherwick.
Goodnight. Evangeline.

237
00:19:29.837 --> 00:19:32.172
Goodnight. Nanny McPhee.

238
00:19:33.298 --> 00:19:37.511
When Mr Brown said no dinner.
I thought they'd be down in a trice.

239
00:19:37.761 --> 00:19:39.388
They've been ever so quiet.

240
00:19:39.638 --> 00:19:43.517
Don't you fret.
They don't dare come in this kitchen.

241
00:19:43.767 --> 00:19:46.353
I have it in writing.

242
00:19:50.482 --> 00:19:52.276
Be careful. Aggy.

243
00:19:52.526 --> 00:19:53.986
It's Mama's rattle.

244
00:19:54.069 --> 00:19:57.406
and it's the only thing
we've got of hers.

245
00:20:00.242 --> 00:20:03.328
- What on earth are you doing?
- Getting ready for bed.

246
00:20:03.579 --> 00:20:07.583
- What she told us to do.
- Since when did we do what we're told?

247
00:20:07.791 --> 00:20:10.627
Since we nearly got Cook blown up
and Aggy boiled.

248
00:20:12.588 --> 00:20:17.467
May I just remind you of something?
We got rid of the last 1 7 nannies.

249
00:20:17.676 --> 00:20:19.887
We're getting rid of this one too.

250
00:20:22.556 --> 00:20:24.850
Fine! Be brave. then!

251
00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:30.105
Yes. well. I nearly got blown up!
And anyway. l...

252
00:20:36.612 --> 00:20:37.988
Hm.

253
00:20:55.339 --> 00:20:59.301
You must feel at such a disadvantage.
Nanny McPhee.

254
00:20:59.551 --> 00:21:00.719
In what way?

255
00:21:00.969 --> 00:21:03.847
We know your name
but you don't know ours.

256
00:21:06.767 --> 00:21:09.645
Pleased to meet you.
I'm Oglington Fartworthy.

257
00:21:18.237 --> 00:21:21.240
How do you do?

258
00:21:23.116 --> 00:21:25.452
That's F-A-R-T.

259
00:21:25.702 --> 00:21:29.414
Fartworthy.

260
00:21:31.333 --> 00:21:34.002
Booger McHorsefanny.

261
00:21:34.253 --> 00:21:36.463
Knickers O'Muffin.

262
00:21:36.672 --> 00:21:37.923
Sandra.

263
00:21:38.173 --> 00:21:39.216
Bum.

264
00:21:39.466 --> 00:21:41.635
I'm Bum!

265
00:21:41.885 --> 00:21:43.637
Oh. Bosoms.

266
00:21:47.349 --> 00:21:48.433
Bum.

267
00:21:48.684 --> 00:21:53.021
You can't be Bum. Aggy.
Sebastian's Bum. You're Poop.

268
00:21:53.272 --> 00:21:54.565
Poop Bum.

269
00:21:54.815 --> 00:21:56.900
You can't be Poop and Bum.

270
00:22:17.588 --> 00:22:19.715
Goodnight. Agatha.

271
00:22:27.181 --> 00:22:29.641
Goodnight. Sebastian.

272
00:22:29.850 --> 00:22:31.935
Goodnight. Tora.

273
00:22:32.186 --> 00:22:34.229
Goodnight. Christianna.

274
00:22:35.814 --> 00:22:37.774
Goodnight. Lily.

275
00:22:38.025 --> 00:22:39.902
Goodnight. Eric.

276
00:22:43.405 --> 00:22:45.490
Goodnight. Simon.

277
00:22:51.246 --> 00:22:55.667
There is something you should understand
about the way I work.

278
00:22:55.918 --> 00:23:00.297
When you need me but do not want me.
then I must stay.

279
00:23:00.547 --> 00:23:06.678
When you want me but no longer need me.
then I have to go.

280
00:23:11.099 --> 00:23:14.019
It's rather sad.
really. but there it is.

281
00:23:15.187 --> 00:23:18.065
We will never want you.

282
00:23:19.566 --> 00:23:21.777
Then I will never go.

283
00:23:26.823 --> 00:23:29.701
Goodnight. children.

284
00:23:33.038 --> 00:23:36.542
How did she know our names?
No one ever knows our names.

285
00:23:36.792 --> 00:23:38.585
- Magic.
- Witchcraft.

286
00:23:38.836 --> 00:23:42.673
It doesn't matter.
We're getting rid of her tomorrow.

287
00:23:51.640 --> 00:23:56.520
What? Wha... What? What?

288
00:23:56.770 --> 00:23:58.730
I did knock.

289
00:23:58.981 --> 00:24:02.734
Of course. You weren't just
creeping up on me. What a suggestion.

290
00:24:02.985 --> 00:24:05.988
The children are
all in bed and asleep.

291
00:24:06.071 --> 00:24:06.989
Good. Really?

292
00:24:07.239 --> 00:24:08.949
Hm.

293
00:24:10.200 --> 00:24:13.579
- Good grief.
- I shall see myself to my room.

294
00:24:13.829 --> 00:24:15.664
Goodnight. Mr Brown.

295
00:24:20.669 --> 00:24:22.588
No. wait.

296
00:24:23.881 --> 00:24:26.925
What do you... I mean. how...
What are your terms?

297
00:24:28.635 --> 00:24:31.763
Your children require five lessons.

298
00:24:32.014 --> 00:24:36.101
Lesson one. to go to bed
when they're told. is complete.

299
00:24:36.351 --> 00:24:40.647
As for my terms.
I take Sunday afternoons off.

300
00:24:41.773 --> 00:24:44.109
Goodnight.

301
00:24:46.069 --> 00:24:47.362
Interesting.

302
00:25:02.669 --> 00:25:04.505
Time to get up.

303
00:25:05.714 --> 00:25:07.841
No.

304
00:25:10.719 --> 00:25:14.181
Hm. I shall give you
half an hour to be up.

305
00:25:14.431 --> 00:25:17.935
washed. dressed. teeth
cleaned. beds made

306
00:25:18.185 --> 00:25:19.561
and out into the garden...

307
00:25:19.686 --> 00:25:21.897
for healthful fresh
air before breakfast.

308
00:25:22.147 --> 00:25:26.818
Lessons start at nine...sharp.

309
00:25:29.238 --> 00:25:33.534
I don't know about you lot.
but I want to stay in bed.

310
00:25:33.784 --> 00:25:37.412
Sebastian. run the thermometer
under the hot tap.

311
00:25:37.663 --> 00:25:41.291
Chrissie. chalk. Eric.
crayons. Lily. pepper.

312
00:25:41.542 --> 00:25:44.586
How do you know
she won't do something horrid to us?

313
00:25:44.837 --> 00:25:46.296
I worked it out.

314
00:25:46.547 --> 00:25:50.801
She's a trained hypnotist.
That's how she made us do those things.

315
00:25:51.051 --> 00:25:53.929
Don't look directly at her
and she can't hypnotise us.

316
00:25:55.681 --> 00:25:56.890
- Morning. Mr Brown.
- Morning.

317
00:25:57.140 --> 00:25:59.893
I'm off to work early.
We're busy at the mortuary.

318
00:26:00.143 --> 00:26:02.437
Some bout of influenza at Archway...

319
00:26:02.563 --> 00:26:05.524
is carrying off all the
old folks... Ah-ah-ah!

320
00:26:05.774 --> 00:26:09.069
Still. what's bad for them
is good for us.

321
00:26:09.319 --> 00:26:11.113
Poor things.

322
00:26:11.363 --> 00:26:14.032
Well. I know. That. too. Of course.

323
00:26:17.202 --> 00:26:20.706
Odd. She normally says.
"Have a nice day."

324
00:26:20.956 --> 00:26:24.042
or "Don't forget your
jacket" if it's cold out.

325
00:26:24.293 --> 00:26:27.337
Very odd. Most peculiar.

326
00:26:29.464 --> 00:26:31.884
Hm.

327
00:26:33.010 --> 00:26:36.597
- I did knock.
- Did you? I didn't hear.

328
00:26:36.847 --> 00:26:38.432
I was talking to...

329
00:26:41.101 --> 00:26:42.936
Never mind.

330
00:26:43.187 --> 00:26:46.106
I believe the children
will be staying in bed today.

331
00:26:46.356 --> 00:26:49.151
The children? What. all day?
Are they ill? What's wrong?

332
00:26:49.401 --> 00:26:52.863
Nothing. I know precisely what to do.
Please leave it to me.

333
00:26:53.113 --> 00:26:55.407
You managed them splendidly last night.

334
00:26:55.657 --> 00:26:57.367
If they are under the weather.

335
00:26:57.618 --> 00:27:00.787
give them what they want.
ice-cream and jelly and suchlike.

336
00:27:01.038 --> 00:27:04.208
My late wife was very particular.
If ever they were ill.

337
00:27:04.458 --> 00:27:06.919
she used to wait on
them hand and foot...

338
00:27:07.044 --> 00:27:08.962
even if they weren't ill at all.

339
00:27:09.213 --> 00:27:13.550
I shall be sure to give them
exactly what they need.

340
00:27:13.800 --> 00:27:18.347
Excellent. Excellent.
Well. I'll just be off to work. then.

341
00:27:29.942 --> 00:27:31.610
She's coming!

342
00:27:31.860 --> 00:27:34.821
Remember. everyone.
don't look in her eyes.

343
00:27:39.368 --> 00:27:40.661
Dear me.

344
00:27:40.911 --> 00:27:45.040
We can't get up. We're ill.

345
00:27:45.290 --> 00:27:47.417
Colds in our doses.

346
00:27:47.668 --> 00:27:49.169
And kemperakurk.

347
00:27:49.419 --> 00:27:52.005
We think it bight be the beasles.

348
00:27:52.256 --> 00:27:53.757
Got measig.

349
00:27:54.007 --> 00:27:56.593
Good heavens.

350
00:27:56.844 --> 00:28:00.013
Then there is of course
no question of your getting up.

351
00:28:00.264 --> 00:28:05.769
I'm very sorry to have to tell you all
that you'll have to stay in bed.

352
00:28:09.815 --> 00:28:10.941
Hm.

353
00:28:30.169 --> 00:28:33.172
- Ah.
- I don't feel well.

354
00:28:33.422 --> 00:28:38.051
- I think I've got a temperature.
- Don't be daft.

355
00:28:40.637 --> 00:28:42.472
Simon. I can't get up.

356
00:28:42.723 --> 00:28:45.767
- You must have looked at her. then.
- I did not look.

357
00:28:46.018 --> 00:28:50.647
I was under the covers the whole time.
Simon. I can't get up either.

358
00:28:50.898 --> 00:28:53.775
- I can't get up!
- I'm stuck like glue!

359
00:28:54.026 --> 00:28:55.611
I'm stuck. too!

360
00:28:57.571 --> 00:29:01.617
Hypnosis. eh? Bang goes that theory.

361
00:29:05.913 --> 00:29:07.623
Good morning.

362
00:29:16.173 --> 00:29:18.842
Morning. Mr B!

363
00:29:19.051 --> 00:29:21.512
Good morning. Mr Jowls. Mr Wheen.

364
00:29:21.762 --> 00:29:25.432
- Thought we'd get you that time.
- No. not this time.

365
00:29:25.682 --> 00:29:30.062
- Nice tea dance. Mr B?
- Ooh. lovely. I shouldn't wonder.

366
00:29:30.312 --> 00:29:33.607
No. I didn't even get there. Disaster.
Children. you know.

367
00:29:33.857 --> 00:29:36.443
- We do know.
- We've said it before.

368
00:29:36.693 --> 00:29:40.030
It's not funerals
you should be in the business of.

369
00:29:40.280 --> 00:29:42.574
It's christenings.

370
00:29:51.250 --> 00:29:55.420
Good morning.
Just excuse me a moment. would you?

371
00:29:55.671 --> 00:29:57.965
Cedric.
let me not beat about the bush.

372
00:29:58.215 --> 00:29:59.842
Your children are out of control.

373
00:30:00.092 --> 00:30:03.554
You need a wife
and your children need a mother.

374
00:30:03.804 --> 00:30:07.224
If you do not remarry by
the end of the month.

375
00:30:07.349 --> 00:30:09.393
steps will have to be taken.

376
00:30:09.643 --> 00:30:12.604
Oh. dear. Oh. dear. oh. dear. oh. dear.

377
00:30:14.523 --> 00:30:17.276
What's your wife like?

378
00:30:17.526 --> 00:30:22.072
Never mind. Less than a month to go.
There's nothing for it.

379
00:30:22.322 --> 00:30:26.410
It'll have to be that woman...
the dreadful one.

380
00:30:27.661 --> 00:30:31.999
Mr Jowls. do you recollect
that...enthusiastic lady?

381
00:30:32.249 --> 00:30:36.837
Mrs Swiftly. was it? Or was it
Mrs Thadius something last year?

382
00:30:37.087 --> 00:30:40.007
- Mrs Thadius Quickly?
- Oh. don't.

383
00:30:40.257 --> 00:30:45.095
"Oh. Mr Brown. you are a saint. You have
a lovely look of kindness about you."

384
00:30:45.345 --> 00:30:50.893
What I wouldn't give for a man like you.
Mr Brown. in my hour of need.

385
00:30:52.436 --> 00:30:54.354
- That one?
- Yes. that one.

386
00:30:54.605 --> 00:30:57.107
We buried Mr Quickly last autumn.
Poor devil.

387
00:30:57.357 --> 00:31:00.986
- He was happy to go.
- He was her third.

388
00:31:01.236 --> 00:31:04.990
You don't happen to know
if... if she ever...ever. erm...

389
00:31:05.240 --> 00:31:07.701
remarried? You know. number four?

390
00:31:07.951 --> 00:31:10.204
Mr Brown. you're not
thinking what I think...

391
00:31:10.329 --> 00:31:12.080
you're thinking. are you. Mr Brown?

392
00:31:13.540 --> 00:31:16.084
Good grief. no! No. no. No. No.

393
00:31:16.335 --> 00:31:20.380
No. No. no... no. What
a thought. No. No.

394
00:31:23.217 --> 00:31:25.552
What's that?

395
00:31:25.802 --> 00:31:29.264
Measle medicine.
to be administered once an hour.

396
00:31:29.515 --> 00:31:31.975
Actually. I'm not sure it is measles.

397
00:31:32.226 --> 00:31:35.187
How can it be anything other?

398
00:31:35.437 --> 00:31:38.106
The chalky-white faces. the livid spots.

399
00:31:38.357 --> 00:31:41.818
the temperatures of 1 20 degrees.

400
00:31:42.069 --> 00:31:45.239
I've seen it time and again. Measles.

401
00:31:46.740 --> 00:31:48.784
Definitely.

402
00:31:56.375 --> 00:32:00.796
- Open.
- Simon. don't!

403
00:32:01.046 --> 00:32:03.340
I'm not taking that.

404
00:32:03.590 --> 00:32:06.176
Then you will not get any better.

405
00:32:06.426 --> 00:32:08.136
Believe me.

406
00:32:08.387 --> 00:32:10.764
It's moving!

407
00:32:12.224 --> 00:32:14.601
Open wide.

408
00:32:16.770 --> 00:32:18.397
Wider.

409
00:32:35.038 --> 00:32:37.332
Simon. spit it out!

410
00:32:37.583 --> 00:32:40.002
You'll have to swallow
it sooner or later.

411
00:32:40.085 --> 00:32:42.045
so I suggest you get it over with.

412
00:32:48.218 --> 00:32:51.680
Very good. Who's next?

413
00:32:52.890 --> 00:32:54.224
"Took..."

414
00:32:54.474 --> 00:32:56.101
"He..."

415
00:32:56.351 --> 00:32:59.229
"He took her lovingly..."

416
00:32:59.479 --> 00:33:04.318
"He took her lovingly
by the...the hand."

417
00:33:04.568 --> 00:33:09.364
Oh! Nanny McPhee. you startled me.

418
00:33:09.615 --> 00:33:11.033
It was that quiet.

419
00:33:11.283 --> 00:33:15.621
I just got to practising my sounds.
Lily's teaching me to read.

420
00:33:15.871 --> 00:33:17.164
That is good.

421
00:33:17.414 --> 00:33:21.585
They're all good... underneath it all.

422
00:33:22.961 --> 00:33:27.424
- A favourite of yours?
- Don't know.

423
00:33:27.674 --> 00:33:29.718
I haven't finished it yet.

424
00:33:29.968 --> 00:33:33.263
The stepmother's a
bit of a horror. though.

425
00:33:33.388 --> 00:33:34.139
Oh. indeed.

426
00:33:34.389 --> 00:33:36.892
It's a pity stories
aren't about real people.

427
00:33:37.142 --> 00:33:41.104
This one seems a farm girl.
but I'll bet a pound to a penny

428
00:33:41.355 --> 00:33:45.150
he finds out she's
really an educated lady.

429
00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:47.694
And then he falls for her.

430
00:33:47.945 --> 00:33:50.030
You must read it and find out.

431
00:33:50.280 --> 00:33:53.158
He wouldn't love her
if she couldn't read.

432
00:33:53.408 --> 00:33:56.578
He'd think her stupid

433
00:33:56.828 --> 00:34:00.874
and worthless and beneath him.

434
00:34:01.124 --> 00:34:02.209
Hm.

435
00:34:17.558 --> 00:34:21.937
Buttered spuds for lunch
with boiled beef. apple pie and custard.

436
00:34:22.187 --> 00:34:24.439
Hm.

437
00:34:26.108 --> 00:34:30.362
I think the children will be requiring
something a little more...

438
00:34:30.612 --> 00:34:32.489
austere today.

439
00:34:32.739 --> 00:34:34.408
'Orse what?

440
00:34:34.658 --> 00:34:38.537
The children are not quite themselves.
Mrs Blatherwick.

441
00:34:38.787 --> 00:34:40.831
God! That means jellies and ice-cream.

442
00:34:40.956 --> 00:34:43.208
raspberry cordial and
God knows what else.

443
00:34:43.458 --> 00:34:46.003
Well. I'd better get cracking. then.

444
00:34:46.253 --> 00:34:48.380
Evangeline!

445
00:34:48.630 --> 00:34:50.841
Where is that lump?

446
00:34:51.091 --> 00:34:52.384
It'll be snow in August...

447
00:34:52.467 --> 00:34:54.595
before that one's there
when you need her.

448
00:34:54.845 --> 00:34:59.683
Calm yourself. Mrs Blatherwick.
I'm in charge today.

449
00:34:59.933 --> 00:35:04.271
I understand that you were once
in the armed forces.

450
00:35:06.815 --> 00:35:10.903
I was that. Cooked at a training camp
in Gloucestershire.

451
00:35:11.153 --> 00:35:13.280
Kept those boys strong. I did.

452
00:35:13.530 --> 00:35:19.119
I'm sure you did. Perhaps a broth
of some sort for the children.

453
00:35:19.369 --> 00:35:21.455
You must be an expert.

454
00:35:21.705 --> 00:35:24.541
Best thin potato gruel with peelings in?

455
00:35:24.791 --> 00:35:27.336
That always got 'em groaning
but kept 'em strong.

456
00:35:27.586 --> 00:35:29.671
Are you well supplied with peelings?

457
00:35:35.177 --> 00:35:37.262
These'll do. Only a day old.

458
00:35:43.644 --> 00:35:47.064
A bit of gristle for
flavour. Ever so tasty.

459
00:35:49.191 --> 00:35:50.567
Get that down you.

460
00:35:50.692 --> 00:35:54.071
There's a lot of goodness
in a turkey neck.

461
00:35:54.321 --> 00:35:56.448
That'll put the hairs
back on your chest.

462
00:35:56.698 --> 00:35:57.950
Smell that.

463
00:35:58.033 --> 00:36:03.038
That is the smell that
forged this empire.

464
00:36:03.247 --> 00:36:07.543
That pong is the pong of conquerors.

465
00:36:07.793 --> 00:36:10.921
All right. men. As you were.

466
00:36:12.673 --> 00:36:15.509
They actually are starving us.

467
00:36:15.759 --> 00:36:19.012
I wonder how long it will
take for us all to die.

468
00:36:35.195 --> 00:36:38.031
Quickly...

469
00:36:38.240 --> 00:36:41.660
Quickly. Quickly. Quickly...

470
00:36:41.869 --> 00:36:44.454
Mrs Selma Quickly.

471
00:36:50.544 --> 00:36:53.630
Have you lazy lot been in bed all day?

472
00:36:53.839 --> 00:36:55.674
Evangeline.

473
00:36:55.924 --> 00:36:58.093
You've been doing measles. haven't you?

474
00:36:58.343 --> 00:37:00.596
The situation's very simple. Evangeline.

475
00:37:00.846 --> 00:37:04.016
The nanny. who in my opinion is a witch.

476
00:37:04.266 --> 00:37:06.977
made us ill and fed
us boiled-down toads.

477
00:37:07.227 --> 00:37:11.106
Nanny McPhee is not a witch. Eric.
You're very naughty to say so.

478
00:37:11.356 --> 00:37:13.567
I'm sure she knew what she was doing.

479
00:37:13.817 --> 00:37:17.529
- She must be fully trained.
- Yes. but as what?

480
00:37:17.779 --> 00:37:20.324
I'm unbelievably hungry. Evangeline.

481
00:37:20.574 --> 00:37:25.078
Can you please get us
something decent to eat?

482
00:37:25.329 --> 00:37:27.623
Did you just say "please"?

483
00:37:27.873 --> 00:37:30.000
Please. please. Evangeline!

484
00:37:31.835 --> 00:37:35.297
Well. children.
I hear you've been in bed all day

485
00:37:35.547 --> 00:37:37.132
but that you're better now.

486
00:37:37.382 --> 00:37:39.593
It wasn't our fault.

487
00:37:39.843 --> 00:37:43.764
I'm sure it wasn't anybody's fault.
You can't help it if you're ill.

488
00:37:44.014 --> 00:37:45.807
But you're better now.

489
00:37:58.612 --> 00:37:59.988
- Papa?
- Yes. Chrissie?

490
00:38:00.239 --> 00:38:03.367
Now that we're better. can we get up?

491
00:38:03.617 --> 00:38:06.578
Can we get up. please?

492
00:38:16.213 --> 00:38:18.382
Of course you can.

493
00:38:18.632 --> 00:38:20.259
Read to us.

494
00:38:20.509 --> 00:38:23.804
I. erm... I have my
letter-writing to do. I...

495
00:38:25.514 --> 00:38:29.726
I'll read to you tomorrow.
Goodnight. my dears.

496
00:38:35.482 --> 00:38:36.525
Evangeline.

497
00:38:36.775 --> 00:38:40.654
please ask Cook to make the children
scrambled eggs on toast.

498
00:38:40.904 --> 00:38:43.782
I'm sure they'd like supper
now they're feeling better.

499
00:38:44.032 --> 00:38:47.160
I'll do it myself. Nanny McPhee.

500
00:38:55.294 --> 00:38:57.337
Didn't she have two bumpy things?

501
00:38:57.588 --> 00:38:59.631
The word is "wart".

502
00:38:59.882 --> 00:39:03.468
Traditionally associated with witches.
as it happens.

503
00:39:03.677 --> 00:39:06.054
Well. one of 'em's gone.

504
00:39:17.774 --> 00:39:19.776
I did knock.

505
00:39:20.027 --> 00:39:21.987
Of course you did.

506
00:39:22.237 --> 00:39:26.241
Lesson two. to get up when they're told.
is complete.

507
00:39:26.491 --> 00:39:28.577
Of course. Very good. Thank you.

508
00:39:28.827 --> 00:39:30.913
Goodnight. Mr Brown.

509
00:39:32.456 --> 00:39:34.958
- Nanny McPhee...
- Yes. Mr Brown?

510
00:39:35.209 --> 00:39:37.461
Didn't you used to have two...

511
00:39:39.588 --> 00:39:41.965
w...w...?

512
00:39:45.052 --> 00:39:48.055
Never mind. It's. er...
it's my imagination.

513
00:39:57.606 --> 00:40:00.359
There was a telegram. Mr Brown.

514
00:40:08.784 --> 00:40:11.119
Oh. my... Oh. my goodness.

515
00:40:14.581 --> 00:40:16.583
- Ah. Nanny McPhee.
- Pa!

516
00:40:16.834 --> 00:40:20.504
Good. good. good.
All right. I have an announcement.

517
00:40:20.754 --> 00:40:22.172
Yes...

518
00:40:22.381 --> 00:40:25.467
Your Great-Aunt Adelaide
is coming for tea today.

519
00:40:27.302 --> 00:40:30.013
- No!
- Aunt Adelaide is vile and vicious.

520
00:40:30.222 --> 00:40:31.306
She's blind as a bat.

521
00:40:31.431 --> 00:40:33.684
And we are convalescing.
for heaven's sake!

522
00:40:33.892 --> 00:40:35.978
That's enough. I don't want to hear...

523
00:40:36.103 --> 00:40:38.355
anything bad about her.
She pays the rent.

524
00:40:38.564 --> 00:40:42.025
- She scares me.
- She's only coming for tea.

525
00:40:42.234 --> 00:40:44.570
You'll all put your best clothes on

526
00:40:44.778 --> 00:40:47.281
and Nanny McPhee will keep you in order.

527
00:40:47.531 --> 00:40:51.827
I shall do my best. sir.
considering that today is Sunday

528
00:40:52.077 --> 00:40:54.162
and I am off duty this afternoon.

529
00:40:54.413 --> 00:40:56.081
Off duty?

530
00:40:58.458 --> 00:41:00.919
You're off duty when...?

531
00:41:01.170 --> 00:41:04.089
You can't be off duty.
I need you. They need you.

532
00:41:04.339 --> 00:41:06.258
I shall be leaving at noon.

533
00:41:06.508 --> 00:41:09.178
Thereafter. I'm sure
the children will do...

534
00:41:09.261 --> 00:41:12.014
exactly as they're told.
Won't you. children?

535
00:41:13.765 --> 00:41:16.852
Listen to this. dear.
Aunt Adelaide says.

536
00:41:17.102 --> 00:41:19.605
"l am coming with the express intention

537
00:41:19.855 --> 00:41:22.816
of easing your financial burden."

538
00:41:23.066 --> 00:41:27.154
Maybe she's thought the better
of my having to remarry.

539
00:41:27.404 --> 00:41:30.157
Perhaps I won't have
to go through with it.

540
00:41:47.090 --> 00:41:50.427
I hate my best clothes.
They're itchy.

541
00:41:50.677 --> 00:41:52.679
Well. we promised. so that's that.

542
00:41:53.805 --> 00:41:56.975
Tora's right.
We should do exactly as we're told.

543
00:41:57.226 --> 00:42:01.313
We've been told to put
our best clothes on. haven't we? Right.

544
00:42:01.563 --> 00:42:06.652
Well. I'm going to put
my best clothes on...the pig.

545
00:42:06.902 --> 00:42:08.153
Simon. no.

546
00:42:08.403 --> 00:42:11.990
- Yeah. the pig!
- Oh. please. don't!

547
00:42:19.498 --> 00:42:22.709
- Aunt Adelaide. welcome back.
- Where are you?

548
00:42:22.960 --> 00:42:26.213
- Here I am. Aunt Adelaide.
- Oh! Don't crowd me so.

549
00:42:26.463 --> 00:42:30.592
You're looking very peely-wally.
Where's my tea? I must have tea.

550
00:42:30.843 --> 00:42:32.469
Of course. This way. At once.

551
00:42:34.179 --> 00:42:35.639
I smell damp.

552
00:42:35.848 --> 00:42:39.560
No. no... At least not noticeably.

553
00:42:39.810 --> 00:42:42.312
Damp in the house.
Hence your pallid complexion.

554
00:42:42.563 --> 00:42:43.522
Lovely hat.

555
00:42:43.772 --> 00:42:47.568
A gift from the Duchess of Kent.
She has taste.

556
00:42:47.818 --> 00:42:50.821
I've always hated this room.

557
00:42:51.071 --> 00:42:52.573
- Milk?
- Certainly not.

558
00:42:52.823 --> 00:42:55.117
Filthy stuff. Most unhealthy.

559
00:42:55.367 --> 00:42:57.661
- Sugar?
- Six. if you please.

560
00:42:57.911 --> 00:42:59.413
Six.

561
00:42:59.663 --> 00:43:04.710
Let me not beat about the bush. Cedric.
You have too many children.

562
00:43:04.960 --> 00:43:07.337
- Ah. that.
- Don't interrupt.

563
00:43:07.588 --> 00:43:12.843
Your wife. my poor. weak-minded niece.
had no sense of proportion.

564
00:43:13.093 --> 00:43:18.182
However. I know where my duties lie.
I gave her my word that I would help.

565
00:43:18.432 --> 00:43:21.560
As you know. Cedric. my word is my law.

566
00:43:21.768 --> 00:43:24.188
I now propose to help you further.

567
00:43:24.438 --> 00:43:27.524
Oh. thank you. Aunt
Adelaide. Thank you.

568
00:43:27.649 --> 00:43:29.526
Don't interrupt. Sit down.

569
00:43:29.776 --> 00:43:32.362
This is my proposal.

570
00:43:32.613 --> 00:43:36.241
I shall relieve you of
one of your children...

571
00:43:37.367 --> 00:43:40.329
and give it a home with
me at Stitch Manor.

572
00:43:45.834 --> 00:43:48.962
It will require sacrifice on my part.
I realise that.

573
00:43:49.213 --> 00:43:55.135
But as my sainted father always said.
"Duty. Adelaide. always duty."

574
00:43:55.385 --> 00:43:58.931
- You mustn't. I can't possibly...
- Thank me enough. I know.

575
00:43:59.181 --> 00:44:02.893
You must feel quite overwhelmed
by the benefits of such a plan.

576
00:44:03.143 --> 00:44:04.770
Your fortunate daughter.

577
00:44:04.978 --> 00:44:08.565
for it must be a girl
and not one of those other things.

578
00:44:08.815 --> 00:44:12.694
will receive private tuition
in literature. history. deportment

579
00:44:12.945 --> 00:44:16.198
and above all. elocution.

580
00:44:16.448 --> 00:44:21.787
If there's one thing I won't stand for.
it's loose vowels.

581
00:44:23.247 --> 00:44:27.543
What did Papa say? He must have
told her not to even think of it.

582
00:44:27.793 --> 00:44:30.212
He didn't say anything.

583
00:44:33.799 --> 00:44:37.135
Come on. Let's find the others.

584
00:44:37.344 --> 00:44:40.931
I must be frank.
There is no question of your taking...

585
00:44:41.181 --> 00:44:44.476
Hush now! I'm used to
taking responsibility...

586
00:44:44.601 --> 00:44:46.562
for other people's mistakes.

587
00:44:46.812 --> 00:44:51.400
Now. where is the bulk
of your offspring?

588
00:44:57.865 --> 00:45:01.827
Ah. Here we are.

589
00:45:07.207 --> 00:45:10.419
- It was a bee. A big bee. Erm...
- Good heavens!

590
00:45:12.588 --> 00:45:14.673
Gone now. Phew.

591
00:45:14.882 --> 00:45:18.051
- Hm.
- You're not well. Cedric.

592
00:45:18.302 --> 00:45:21.680
The sooner you find a
good wife. the better.

593
00:45:21.930 --> 00:45:25.726
This'll put her off
wanting any of you girls.

594
00:45:25.976 --> 00:45:28.854
Speak up. girl!

595
00:45:29.104 --> 00:45:32.816
Oh! What an unfortunate face.

596
00:45:33.066 --> 00:45:36.028
All those bristles.

597
00:45:36.278 --> 00:45:39.573
It might be very hard
to get her decently betrothed.

598
00:45:42.117 --> 00:45:44.536
Do you not have a more comely girl?

599
00:45:50.459 --> 00:45:53.837
Perhaps round the front of the house.

600
00:45:57.591 --> 00:46:01.053
Chrissie. hurry up!

601
00:46:03.514 --> 00:46:06.016
Tie it. Chrissie.

602
00:46:06.266 --> 00:46:09.186
Eric. stop her!

603
00:46:09.436 --> 00:46:11.355
- Chrissie. stop! She'll see you!
- Papa!

604
00:46:11.605 --> 00:46:14.858
Cedric. I had no idea
that you had produced such a...

605
00:46:15.108 --> 00:46:18.570
such an unattractive batch of females.

606
00:46:18.820 --> 00:46:22.699
I shall leave directly. Get my hat.

607
00:46:22.950 --> 00:46:25.536
Your hat? So soon?

608
00:46:25.786 --> 00:46:28.664
- Really? No. you can't... I'll get it.
- Hewitt!

609
00:46:31.500 --> 00:46:33.043
No!

610
00:46:37.673 --> 00:46:41.593
Oh. yes. You'll do perfectly.

611
00:46:41.844 --> 00:46:46.723
A little timid. perhaps.
but we'll soon knock that out of you.

612
00:46:46.974 --> 00:46:50.185
Come on. come on. It
can't do any harm to try.

613
00:46:50.435 --> 00:46:53.230
I can't find your... What are you doing?

614
00:46:53.480 --> 00:46:55.774
- This is the chosen one. Get her ready.
- Papa. help!

615
00:46:56.024 --> 00:46:57.818
Chrissie? You're not listen...

616
00:46:57.901 --> 00:47:00.112
Shut up. Cedric. and do as you're told!

617
00:47:00.362 --> 00:47:03.615
Nanny McPhee. we need you.

618
00:47:03.866 --> 00:47:09.454
Nanny McPhee. please. we need you.

619
00:47:09.705 --> 00:47:13.667
Where is my hat?

620
00:47:16.086 --> 00:47:17.462
Hide!

621
00:47:23.385 --> 00:47:25.304
My hat!

622
00:47:25.554 --> 00:47:28.724
How dare you!

623
00:47:38.400 --> 00:47:42.613
- Oh. my. what a merry game.
- Yoo-hoo!

624
00:47:42.863 --> 00:47:45.407
My. my. what a pretty girl you are.

625
00:47:52.956 --> 00:47:55.459
Oh. this is the girl for me.

626
00:47:57.002 --> 00:47:58.504
Run.

627
00:47:58.754 --> 00:48:01.965
Such poise. such gaiety.

628
00:48:02.216 --> 00:48:05.219
- Ah. there you are. staff.
- Yes. madam.

629
00:48:05.469 --> 00:48:09.515
I'm taking this child
with me. Get her ready.

630
00:48:16.647 --> 00:48:18.106
Very well. madam.

631
00:48:18.357 --> 00:48:20.692
Sherry time.

632
00:48:23.445 --> 00:48:27.449
Do not forget that someone
has to go with your great-aunt

633
00:48:27.699 --> 00:48:30.160
and it cannot be the donkey. can it?

634
00:48:40.504 --> 00:48:43.715
Well. I'm the eldest girl. I'll go.

635
00:48:43.966 --> 00:48:48.929
No. I've always known
I was destined for tragedy. I'll go.

636
00:48:49.179 --> 00:48:50.973
Aggy go.

637
00:48:51.223 --> 00:48:54.768
Don't be silly. Aggy.
You're not even a whole girl yet.

638
00:48:55.978 --> 00:48:59.064
No. She wanted me. I'll go.

639
00:48:59.314 --> 00:49:01.400
You can't all go.

640
00:49:12.786 --> 00:49:15.539
Well. I am entirely satisfied.

641
00:49:15.789 --> 00:49:20.294
I will keep my word. Cedric.
if you will keep yours.

642
00:49:20.544 --> 00:49:24.173
You must give those children a mother
before the month is out.

643
00:49:24.423 --> 00:49:25.799
No.

644
00:49:27.718 --> 00:49:28.927
What?

645
00:49:29.178 --> 00:49:33.432
You cannot order me around. And you
certainly can't take any of my children.

646
00:49:33.682 --> 00:49:35.225
l...

647
00:49:35.475 --> 00:49:39.188
Your carriage awaits. madam.

648
00:49:39.438 --> 00:49:41.481
Is the chosen one seated?

649
00:49:41.732 --> 00:49:44.818
- lndeed she is.
- Good.

650
00:49:45.068 --> 00:49:48.655
- All is prepared.
- Which chosen one? What's prepared?

651
00:49:48.906 --> 00:49:51.658
Cedric. in view of this afternoon's
happy outcome.

652
00:49:51.909 --> 00:49:55.537
I am willing to overlook
that last unattractive outburst.

653
00:49:55.787 --> 00:49:58.207
- Nanny McPhee.
- Off we go. Hewitt.

654
00:49:58.457 --> 00:50:01.293
- What have you done?
- I have done nothing. sir.

655
00:50:01.543 --> 00:50:04.004
The children have decided
amongst themselves.

656
00:50:04.254 --> 00:50:06.381
Decided what? What do you mean?

657
00:50:06.632 --> 00:50:08.634
There you are. dear.

658
00:50:08.884 --> 00:50:12.054
Not little Chrissie.

659
00:50:13.222 --> 00:50:14.848
Chrissie!

660
00:50:18.352 --> 00:50:19.728
Chrissie!

661
00:50:21.021 --> 00:50:22.147
Yah!

662
00:50:23.899 --> 00:50:25.275
Chrissie!

663
00:50:30.072 --> 00:50:33.033
Now. then. you'd better
tell me your name. little girl.

664
00:50:37.120 --> 00:50:38.080
Christianna!

665
00:50:38.163 --> 00:50:41.083
Don't be shy. my dear.
What is your name?

666
00:50:45.170 --> 00:50:47.881
Sit up straight and tell me your name.

667
00:50:50.259 --> 00:50:52.302
No!

668
00:50:53.637 --> 00:50:55.556
- Christianna!
- Papa!

669
00:50:55.806 --> 00:50:58.559
Papa! Papa!

670
00:51:01.311 --> 00:51:04.189
Oh!

671
00:51:08.151 --> 00:51:09.695
Then...then who...?

672
00:51:13.532 --> 00:51:17.286
Evangeline. My name's Evangeline.

673
00:51:25.752 --> 00:51:29.756
And what a pretty name it is. too.

674
00:51:33.051 --> 00:51:35.220
Evangeline...

675
00:51:36.930 --> 00:51:38.432
Oh.

676
00:52:00.996 --> 00:52:03.415
Time for bed.

677
00:52:03.624 --> 00:52:07.461
- Thank you for saving me. Nanny McPhee.
- Hm.

678
00:52:09.296 --> 00:52:12.090
Yes. Thank you.

679
00:52:12.299 --> 00:52:14.510
Thank you.

680
00:52:14.718 --> 00:52:17.054
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

681
00:52:33.529 --> 00:52:34.988
Hm.

682
00:52:37.199 --> 00:52:39.993
Papa was going to let her take me.

683
00:52:40.202 --> 00:52:45.040
No. Christianna.
Your father would never have allowed it.

684
00:52:52.840 --> 00:52:56.635
- Goodnight. children.
- Goodnight. Nanny McPhee.

685
00:53:01.098 --> 00:53:03.392
She hasn't got any warts at all now.

686
00:53:03.600 --> 00:53:06.478
Do you think she's using
some sort of cream?

687
00:53:34.631 --> 00:53:38.135
Thank you. Nanny McPhee.
You were a tremendous help.

688
00:53:38.343 --> 00:53:39.636
Not at all.

689
00:53:39.845 --> 00:53:41.930
You will find that lesson three.

690
00:53:42.139 --> 00:53:45.559
to get dressed when they're told.
is complete.

691
00:53:45.767 --> 00:53:48.145
Just to get dressed when they're told?

692
00:53:48.228 --> 00:53:50.981
They've learned a great
deal more than that.

693
00:53:52.608 --> 00:53:54.776
I have five lessons to teach.

694
00:53:54.985 --> 00:53:59.531
What lessons they learn is entirely
up to them. Goodnight. Mr Brown.

695
00:53:59.740 --> 00:54:03.660
- Nanny McPhee...
- Yes. Mr Brown?

696
00:54:03.869 --> 00:54:08.248
She will be all right. won't she?
Evangeline. I mean.

697
00:54:09.791 --> 00:54:12.920
I can't help being concerned.

698
00:54:13.128 --> 00:54:17.174
Aunt Adelaide can be so. erm...
Well. you saw.

699
00:54:17.382 --> 00:54:19.885
She will certainly be all right.

700
00:54:20.093 --> 00:54:22.638
Good.

701
00:54:22.846 --> 00:54:25.224
I suppose she volunteered
to go. did she?

702
00:54:25.349 --> 00:54:27.809
Couldn't wait to be
shot of us. I imagine.

703
00:54:28.018 --> 00:54:29.853
Not quite.

704
00:54:30.062 --> 00:54:31.605
It was Simon's idea.

705
00:54:31.813 --> 00:54:34.316
He knew Evangeline
might like to educate herself

706
00:54:34.525 --> 00:54:37.694
and that her going
would save Christianna.

707
00:54:37.903 --> 00:54:39.696
He's a very clever boy.

708
00:54:39.905 --> 00:54:41.865
Good heavens. Simon. eh?

709
00:54:41.949 --> 00:54:45.494
Well. good for him.
Quick...quick thinking.

710
00:54:45.702 --> 00:54:47.996
Goodnight. Mr Brown.

711
00:55:02.386 --> 00:55:04.972
So that's it. then.

712
00:55:05.180 --> 00:55:08.141
I shall have to marry...Quickly.

713
00:56:00.944 --> 00:56:04.281
Children. your father
has asked me to tell you

714
00:56:04.489 --> 00:56:08.368
there's a Mrs Quickly
coming for tea tomorrow.

715
00:56:09.453 --> 00:56:13.373
- Nanny McPhee?
- Yes. sweetheart?

716
00:56:13.582 --> 00:56:17.961
Can you stop Papa
from marrying a horrible stepmother?

717
00:56:20.088 --> 00:56:21.798
I'm afraid not.

718
00:56:22.007 --> 00:56:27.346
- Even if you wanted to?
- Even if I wanted to.

719
00:56:27.554 --> 00:56:32.434
I cannot interfere with
affairs of the heart.

720
00:56:39.942 --> 00:56:42.402
Perhaps Simon could
talk to him about it.

721
00:56:42.611 --> 00:56:44.821
He won't listen.

722
00:56:56.416 --> 00:56:58.669
You have a visitor. Mr Brown.

723
00:56:58.877 --> 00:57:02.464
An especially eager visitor. Mr Brown.

724
00:57:11.932 --> 00:57:15.394
Quickly by name...

725
00:57:15.602 --> 00:57:16.728
Oh!

726
00:57:16.937 --> 00:57:19.106
Simon. my boy.

727
00:57:19.314 --> 00:57:21.567
Well. come in.

728
00:57:21.775 --> 00:57:23.735
Come on. I won't bite.

729
00:57:26.780 --> 00:57:30.826
- Father. we want to ask you something.
- Well. of course.

730
00:57:31.034 --> 00:57:33.078
Of course. Anything at all. Ask away.

731
00:57:33.287 --> 00:57:35.998
Who is Mrs Quickly?

732
00:57:37.541 --> 00:57:41.378
Good heavens. such a face. She's. er...

733
00:57:41.587 --> 00:57:44.339
She's...she's a friend.
She's...a friend.

734
00:57:44.548 --> 00:57:46.466
Just a friend?

735
00:57:46.675 --> 00:57:47.384
Well. my boy.

736
00:57:47.467 --> 00:57:50.053
it's not exactly any of
your business. is it?

737
00:57:50.262 --> 00:57:52.514
It is if she's to be our new mother.

738
00:57:52.723 --> 00:57:54.516
Who said anything about that?

739
00:57:54.725 --> 00:57:57.644
It is true? You are going to marry her?

740
00:57:59.313 --> 00:58:01.064
You go too far. Simon.

741
00:58:01.273 --> 00:58:03.775
- You must not question...
- I didn't.

742
00:58:03.984 --> 00:58:05.694
- Don't contradict me!
- I'm not!

743
00:58:05.903 --> 00:58:08.822
You do not understand the adult world.

744
00:58:09.031 --> 00:58:11.992
You know. there are
certain things that...

745
00:58:12.201 --> 00:58:14.912
certain things...

746
00:58:15.120 --> 00:58:17.497
You will leave me this instant. Go home!

747
00:58:20.250 --> 00:58:22.294
You never listen!

748
00:58:51.782 --> 00:58:53.784
Nanny McPhee?

749
00:58:56.662 --> 00:58:58.789
Nanny McPhee?

750
01:00:03.353 --> 01:00:05.731
Hello. Simon.

751
01:00:05.939 --> 01:00:07.524
Can I help you?

752
01:00:07.733 --> 01:00:09.860
I did knock.

753
01:00:10.068 --> 01:00:13.280
I know. I heard you.

754
01:00:16.867 --> 01:00:19.286
May I be of assistance?

755
01:00:22.998 --> 01:00:26.210
We need you to. erm...

756
01:00:26.418 --> 01:00:28.837
I mean...you saved Chrissie.

757
01:00:29.922 --> 01:00:31.757
And so...

758
01:00:31.965 --> 01:00:34.843
You're on our side. is what I mean.

759
01:00:35.052 --> 01:00:37.012
Aren't you?

760
01:00:37.221 --> 01:00:41.934
You saved Chrissie. and
I do not take sides.

761
01:00:43.810 --> 01:00:50.025
I...we... need you to help us
get rid of this woman. Mrs Quickly.

762
01:00:50.234 --> 01:00:55.781
It will not surprise you to hear
that I cannot agree to that. Simon.

763
01:00:55.989 --> 01:00:59.910
Then let us do whatever
we have to do to get rid of her.

764
01:01:00.118 --> 01:01:03.956
Are you prepared to accept
the consequences?

765
01:01:04.164 --> 01:01:05.541
Yes.

766
01:01:05.749 --> 01:01:09.711
- You promise?
- Yes. Yes. absolutely. I promise.

767
01:01:13.173 --> 01:01:19.179
Then I will. as you put it.
let you do whatever you have to do.

768
01:01:19.388 --> 01:01:21.181
Thank you.

769
01:01:22.975 --> 01:01:25.477
Thank you.

770
01:01:27.980 --> 01:01:32.401
Look at them! Will
you just look at them?

771
01:01:34.611 --> 01:01:38.782
The little. small things.

772
01:01:39.950 --> 01:01:42.369
Children. this is. er... Mrs Quickly.

773
01:01:42.578 --> 01:01:44.580
Oh. you mustn't be so formal.

774
01:01:44.788 --> 01:01:49.251
You must call me Auntie Selma.

775
01:01:49.459 --> 01:01:53.213
Oh. dear me. one does work up
such a thirst in this heat.

776
01:01:54.548 --> 01:01:56.967
Oh. Tea. of course. Do
go through. I'll...

777
01:01:57.176 --> 01:02:01.221
And leave these dear creatures?
How can you ask it of me?

778
01:02:03.265 --> 01:02:06.643
- Oh. the heart of the house.
- Yes. yes.

779
01:02:06.852 --> 01:02:09.104
- The old bachelor's den.
- Mm.

780
01:02:09.313 --> 01:02:12.524
- Well. l...
- lsn't it enchanting?

781
01:02:12.733 --> 01:02:15.027
Ooh! Have you read all those books?

782
01:02:15.235 --> 01:02:17.279
- Well. l. er...
- Clever.

783
01:02:17.487 --> 01:02:21.700
- Take my chair. It's more comfortable.
- Thank you. Ooh!

784
01:02:21.909 --> 01:02:24.703
Well. what have we here?

785
01:02:24.912 --> 01:02:27.998
I see there is already
provision for a lady.

786
01:02:28.123 --> 01:02:29.708
How thoughtful you are.

787
01:02:29.917 --> 01:02:31.960
What a gentleman.

788
01:02:33.879 --> 01:02:37.883
Wait! Er...just let me
make it. er...comfy for you.

789
01:02:38.091 --> 01:02:39.676
Too. too precious.

790
01:02:39.885 --> 01:02:43.639
Here in the centre of the male dominion.

791
01:02:43.847 --> 01:02:47.226
..an oasis of feminine
charm and elegance.

792
01:02:47.434 --> 01:02:51.813
There. just as I thought. It's dusty.
It just needs a good old thump.

793
01:02:52.022 --> 01:02:55.108
There. All thumped and ready to go.

794
01:02:55.317 --> 01:02:59.655
There you go again.
Nothing is too much trouble for you.

795
01:03:00.864 --> 01:03:05.661
I observed that very characteristic
on the sad day we buried Mr Quickly.

796
01:03:05.869 --> 01:03:09.331
Even in my demented grief.
I said to my friend Letitia Carter...

797
01:03:09.540 --> 01:03:14.086
Remember her? A pinker complexion
than my own. She takes too much sun.

798
01:03:14.294 --> 01:03:18.298
I said. "Kindness seems to be
second nature to him."

799
01:03:18.507 --> 01:03:20.509
"He is a perfect gentleman."

800
01:03:20.717 --> 01:03:24.721
"There's something so masculine
and yet retiring in his manner..."

801
01:03:24.930 --> 01:03:26.765
Mr Brown!

802
01:03:32.271 --> 01:03:34.314
Un moment. I pray you.

803
01:03:34.523 --> 01:03:36.483
I don't know what came over me.

804
01:03:36.692 --> 01:03:40.946
I do. I understand. I
never took you for such.

805
01:03:41.154 --> 01:03:45.951
But now I see it.
Passion is clearly your nature. too.

806
01:03:46.159 --> 01:03:51.290
I feel it. Who would have thought
we were such kindred spirits?

807
01:03:51.498 --> 01:03:53.041
Passion is my life.

808
01:03:53.125 --> 01:03:56.670
In fact. Mr Brown. what
is life without it?

809
01:03:57.629 --> 01:04:01.466
A grey wheel of habit. spinning idly on.

810
01:04:09.683 --> 01:04:13.478
This is no time for
food. Mrs Quickly...

811
01:04:13.604 --> 01:04:14.104
Selma.

812
01:04:14.313 --> 01:04:17.107
I couldn't possibly swallow it
under the circumstances.

813
01:04:17.316 --> 01:04:19.735
You are tempestuous. Mr Brown.

814
01:04:20.944 --> 01:04:24.156
- Tea?
- Yes. tea.

815
01:04:24.364 --> 01:04:28.076
We must blanket the raw impulse
with that reliable beverage.

816
01:04:31.455 --> 01:04:34.124
That's a nice bit of
porcelain. Is that Spode?

817
01:04:34.249 --> 01:04:36.084
I like a bit of Spode. Tasteful.

818
01:04:36.293 --> 01:04:39.922
Anyway. so essential
for upholding the normal...

819
01:04:40.130 --> 01:04:43.550
- You don't want that.
- How right you are.

820
01:04:43.759 --> 01:04:46.428
You see into my inmost self.

821
01:04:46.637 --> 01:04:51.433
What is tea when we can drink
from the nectar of our emotions?

822
01:04:51.642 --> 01:04:53.477
Let the common herd drink tea.

823
01:04:53.685 --> 01:04:57.439
Our souls need a more divine libation!

824
01:05:02.027 --> 01:05:05.239
Oh! You mad fool! I say.

825
01:05:05.447 --> 01:05:08.283
No. no. not here amongst the cutlery.

826
01:05:08.492 --> 01:05:10.786
I say!

827
01:05:12.412 --> 01:05:15.832
I must go before my reputation
is in tatters on this rug.

828
01:05:16.041 --> 01:05:18.252
Lovely rug. Is it Chinese silk?

829
01:05:18.460 --> 01:05:21.046
Must escape before all is lost.

830
01:05:21.255 --> 01:05:22.589
Wait!

831
01:05:22.798 --> 01:05:27.261
Heavens to Betsy! You are inflamed!

832
01:05:27.469 --> 01:05:32.140
How does a lonely widow best you?
What defences does she have?

833
01:05:33.892 --> 01:05:36.812
All it takes is one question. Cedric.
and I'm yours.

834
01:05:37.020 --> 01:05:42.317
- Ask me or you'll lose me forever.
- Oh. no... Absolutely.

835
01:05:42.526 --> 01:05:45.112
Say it. Say it.

836
01:05:45.320 --> 01:05:49.157
- Say it. Say it.
- No!

837
01:05:49.867 --> 01:05:54.371
Oh! No! This is too much. sir!

838
01:05:55.747 --> 01:05:57.875
You are a cad!

839
01:05:59.751 --> 01:06:03.005
A bounder and a cad!

840
01:06:03.797 --> 01:06:06.633
Yeah!

841
01:06:06.842 --> 01:06:08.719
Papa's coming.

842
01:06:20.397 --> 01:06:23.233
She's gone.

843
01:06:23.442 --> 01:06:27.905
The only person in the whole world
who stands between all of us

844
01:06:28.113 --> 01:06:30.782
and total ruin...

845
01:06:30.991 --> 01:06:33.869
and she's gone.

846
01:06:35.412 --> 01:06:37.539
What's ruin?

847
01:06:39.041 --> 01:06:43.670
There's no time to mince words.
I can't support my own family.

848
01:06:43.879 --> 01:06:47.466
I never have been able to.
There are so many of you.

849
01:06:48.800 --> 01:06:50.844
But you're all so delicious.

850
01:06:51.053 --> 01:06:54.473
When Aggy came along
and your mother was so ill. I said.

851
01:06:54.681 --> 01:06:59.019
"We may have to stop now. dear."
and she said...

852
01:06:59.228 --> 01:07:01.730
She said. "l know."

853
01:07:09.363 --> 01:07:12.491
The fact of the matter is.
your Great-Aunt Adelaide

854
01:07:12.699 --> 01:07:16.620
has been supporting us for years
with a monthly allowance.

855
01:07:16.828 --> 01:07:19.248
A little while ago. she told me

856
01:07:19.456 --> 01:07:22.626
that I had to remarry
or the allowance would stop.

857
01:07:22.835 --> 01:07:25.838
This woman today was my last chance.

858
01:07:26.046 --> 01:07:28.173
Our last chance.

859
01:07:28.382 --> 01:07:30.133
Ours?

860
01:07:31.593 --> 01:07:35.264
When the money stops.
the house will be taken.

861
01:07:35.472 --> 01:07:38.892
Some of you will perhaps
be put into the workhouse.

862
01:07:39.101 --> 01:07:43.647
Some will be put into the care...
into the care of others.

863
01:07:44.731 --> 01:07:48.569
I don't know how many of you
will be allowed to stay together.

864
01:07:55.450 --> 01:07:57.494
I'm sorry to have failed you. children.

865
01:08:01.540 --> 01:08:04.126
You deserve so much better.

866
01:08:09.089 --> 01:08:13.135
- Do something.
- What would you suggest?

867
01:08:13.343 --> 01:08:18.265
Change what happened.
Bang your stick. Make it undo itself.

868
01:08:18.473 --> 01:08:20.684
I cannot. These were your actions.

869
01:08:20.893 --> 01:08:24.563
Simon promised that you would
accept the consequences.

870
01:08:24.771 --> 01:08:28.233
What shall we do?
Help us. Tell us what to do.

871
01:08:28.442 --> 01:08:33.030
- You must undo it for yourselves.
- How? How?

872
01:08:33.238 --> 01:08:35.574
Think.

873
01:08:35.782 --> 01:08:38.619
You are very clever. children.

874
01:08:38.827 --> 01:08:40.412
Think.

875
01:08:44.082 --> 01:08:45.459
So. 'e was keen?

876
01:08:45.542 --> 01:08:48.795
Oh. Letty. he was in
a maddened condition.

877
01:08:49.004 --> 01:08:52.174
He couldn't keep his hands off me.
But I held firm.

878
01:08:52.382 --> 01:08:57.221
I said. "Shedric..." I mean. "Cedric.
I have my reputation to uphold."

879
01:08:57.429 --> 01:09:00.349
"It's marriage or nothing.
What do you take me for?"

880
01:09:00.557 --> 01:09:01.850
"Some common...?"

881
01:09:02.059 --> 01:09:04.686
- Tart?
- Not for me. I'm bloated.

882
01:09:04.895 --> 01:09:07.272
No."Some common tart." You said...

883
01:09:07.481 --> 01:09:10.275
Who's that knocking?

884
01:09:10.484 --> 01:09:12.528
It might be him.

885
01:09:14.404 --> 01:09:17.699
If you've come to fumble
with my fastenings... Oh.

886
01:09:19.284 --> 01:09:21.954
Mrs Quickly. we're very
sorry about the tea...

887
01:09:22.037 --> 01:09:23.413
you had with our father.

888
01:09:23.622 --> 01:09:26.041
Typical of a man. sending
his little ones...

889
01:09:26.166 --> 01:09:27.292
to do the dirty work.

890
01:09:27.501 --> 01:09:30.045
No. He doesn't know we're...

891
01:09:30.254 --> 01:09:32.756
I mean. he very much wants to marry you.

892
01:09:32.965 --> 01:09:37.010
I know what he wanted.
No wonder there's so many of you!

893
01:09:37.219 --> 01:09:41.723
Wait. Father wasn't being rude.
No one on earth could be less rude.

894
01:09:41.932 --> 01:09:45.185
He was protecting you from
the naughty things we were doing.

895
01:09:45.394 --> 01:09:48.522
- The toad in the teapot.
- And the wormy sandwiches.

896
01:09:48.730 --> 01:09:52.192
That was my idea! I mean. my fault.

897
01:09:52.401 --> 01:09:55.404
I have no idea to what
you can be referring.

898
01:09:55.612 --> 01:09:59.741
Don't try to make excuses for him.
He's a flounder and a gad.

899
01:09:59.950 --> 01:10:03.453
He's not. He's a good man.
He was just trying to save us.

900
01:10:03.662 --> 01:10:06.206
If he doesn't marry.
all the money will go.

901
01:10:06.290 --> 01:10:08.500
We'll be thrown out onto the streets.

902
01:10:08.709 --> 01:10:12.588
- Money? What money?
- Our Great-Aunt Adelaide's money.

903
01:10:12.796 --> 01:10:15.299
Lady Adelaide Stitch.

904
01:10:15.507 --> 01:10:18.218
Lady? Ooh!

905
01:10:19.511 --> 01:10:21.471
- Mr Brown.
- Mrs Quickly.

906
01:10:21.680 --> 01:10:24.933
- Your children have explained it all.
- Explained?

907
01:10:25.142 --> 01:10:27.436
That their tricks during
tea was a result...

908
01:10:27.561 --> 01:10:29.104
of their motherless condition.

909
01:10:29.313 --> 01:10:31.940
that they need a woman's presence
to calm them.

910
01:10:32.149 --> 01:10:34.902
and that you could benefit
from that presence.

911
01:10:35.110 --> 01:10:37.279
pathetic and lonely as you are.

912
01:10:37.487 --> 01:10:43.535
And all it takes is one
little question. Cedric.

913
01:10:45.996 --> 01:10:49.166
Oh. Oh. y... er...yes. of course.

914
01:10:49.374 --> 01:10:51.752
Erm...just give me...Yes.

915
01:10:53.128 --> 01:10:55.047
- Mrs Quickly...
- Selma.

916
01:10:55.255 --> 01:10:57.132
Yes. I mean Selma.

917
01:10:57.341 --> 01:11:01.512
Would you do me the honour
of becoming my...

918
01:11:04.139 --> 01:11:07.017
- ..of becoming my...
- Wife.

919
01:11:07.226 --> 01:11:12.523
- Exactly. Wife. That's the word.
- Yes. Oh. yes. Cedric.

920
01:11:18.153 --> 01:11:20.948
Off you go now. dears.

921
01:11:21.156 --> 01:11:24.493
Let Daddy have a little
moment to himself...

922
01:11:24.576 --> 01:11:26.078
with your new mummy.

923
01:11:30.082 --> 01:11:33.085
A bit big for this nightie. aren't...

924
01:11:33.210 --> 01:11:35.671
you. sweetheart? We'll
have a new one made.

925
01:11:45.514 --> 01:11:47.558
I'm sorry.

926
01:11:49.893 --> 01:11:53.397
I should have told you.
I can see that now.

927
01:11:53.605 --> 01:11:57.484
If I'd discussed it with you before.
we wouldn't be in this mess.

928
01:11:59.111 --> 01:12:02.072
No. it was our fault.

929
01:12:04.533 --> 01:12:08.412
We should have known you had
a good reason for getting married.

930
01:12:08.620 --> 01:12:11.832
At least this way.
we'll all be together.

931
01:12:11.915 --> 01:12:14.960
That's what matters most. isn't it? Hm?

932
01:12:15.169 --> 01:12:18.547
I promise I'll never hide anything
that affects us from you again.

933
01:12:18.755 --> 01:12:21.842
I see you're more than capable
of understanding it.

934
01:12:23.385 --> 01:12:26.305
- Papa?
- Yes. my boy?

935
01:12:26.513 --> 01:12:30.767
Do you think Mama still thinks about us
where she is?

936
01:12:33.562 --> 01:12:35.814
I'm sure she does.

937
01:12:37.691 --> 01:12:39.818
I know she does.

938
01:12:45.407 --> 01:12:49.453
Now. Chrissie.
why don't you choose us a story?

939
01:12:51.538 --> 01:12:54.124
# Tiptoe by

940
01:12:54.333 --> 01:12:57.878
- # Where my babies lie...
- Lesson four is complete.

941
01:12:58.086 --> 01:13:01.548
# In your tiny silver shoon...

942
01:13:01.757 --> 01:13:04.176
Lesson four?

943
01:13:05.552 --> 01:13:08.096
To listen.

944
01:13:11.099 --> 01:13:12.726
Well done.

945
01:13:12.935 --> 01:13:18.482
# Will you watch over. please

946
01:13:18.690 --> 01:13:21.902
# My wee ones

947
01:13:22.110 --> 01:13:25.531
# My lambkins

948
01:13:25.739 --> 01:13:31.703
# My sweet chick-a-chickadees

949
01:13:32.663 --> 01:13:38.585
# Loola-bye. oh. loola-bye

950
01:13:39.670 --> 01:13:52.307
# In your tiny silver shoon #

951
01:13:57.145 --> 01:14:00.148
The big day.
I do love my weddings.

952
01:14:00.357 --> 01:14:02.943
Mr Brown. What's he really like?

953
01:14:03.151 --> 01:14:05.863
No idea. Keen as mustard
to tie the knot. though.

954
01:14:06.071 --> 01:14:09.825
Had to sort this out quick.
Only got the sheep dipped yesterday.

955
01:14:10.033 --> 01:14:13.871
But he's easily controlled.
unlike his nasty little brood.

956
01:14:14.079 --> 01:14:16.582
However will you manage them. Selma?

957
01:14:16.790 --> 01:14:19.710
I've got a few tricks up my sleeve.
Never you mind.

958
01:14:19.918 --> 01:14:22.880
I started off by giving
them a good clean-up.

959
01:14:23.088 --> 01:14:25.340
Oh. don't they look lovely?

960
01:14:27.259 --> 01:14:30.053
Sebastian. your top button is undone.

961
01:14:30.262 --> 01:14:34.600
Lily. you have a little hair caught
in your crook. Eric. help her. please.

962
01:14:34.808 --> 01:14:37.644
Your father will be down in a moment.

963
01:14:37.853 --> 01:14:42.524
Now. that is an improvement.
Letty. go and keep a lookout.

964
01:14:43.483 --> 01:14:45.694
I say. whatever your name is.

965
01:14:45.903 --> 01:14:49.031
give me a second on my own
with the little darlings?

966
01:14:54.036 --> 01:14:58.874
Now. my dears. there's going to be
some changes made round here.

967
01:15:00.542 --> 01:15:02.878
I'm in charge of this household now

968
01:15:03.086 --> 01:15:07.591
and while I'm in charge.
you children will behave.

969
01:15:07.799 --> 01:15:11.553
Do you hear? Behave.

970
01:15:11.762 --> 01:15:16.141
Behave.

971
01:15:18.477 --> 01:15:21.313
And we're not having any
of that nasty noise...

972
01:15:21.438 --> 01:15:23.607
all the way through my nice wedding.

973
01:15:23.815 --> 01:15:28.737
Shut her up.

974
01:15:30.697 --> 01:15:32.366
Naughty.

975
01:15:32.574 --> 01:15:34.868
It's our mother's rattle. Give it back.

976
01:15:35.077 --> 01:15:37.246
I'm your mother now.

977
01:15:42.876 --> 01:15:44.962
Time to adapt.

978
01:15:54.304 --> 01:15:56.390
Papa. Mrs Quickly...

979
01:15:56.598 --> 01:15:58.767
Yoo-hoo. Cedric.

980
01:15:58.976 --> 01:16:02.521
I realise the bride and groom
shouldn't meet until the ceremony.

981
01:16:02.729 --> 01:16:05.607
but you and I are old hands at this.

982
01:16:05.816 --> 01:16:09.945
She's here! Lady Stitch!

983
01:16:10.153 --> 01:16:11.822
Selma. there's footmen.

984
01:16:13.824 --> 01:16:17.494
Oi. make way!

985
01:16:21.164 --> 01:16:22.624
Where's the woman?

986
01:16:22.833 --> 01:16:26.253
- Aunt Adelaide...
- Shut up! Where's the woman. Cedric?

987
01:16:26.461 --> 01:16:29.173
May I present my...fiancee.
Selma Quickly.

988
01:16:29.298 --> 01:16:31.008
Selma. this is Lady Stitch.

989
01:16:31.216 --> 01:16:35.095
Your Ladyness. Welcome.
if I may be so bold.

990
01:16:35.304 --> 01:16:37.890
to our humble. nay. lowly festivities.

991
01:16:38.098 --> 01:16:41.310
You shower glory upon us from above.

992
01:16:41.518 --> 01:16:45.355
The very air about you shines with...

993
01:16:45.564 --> 01:16:49.735
with...with aboveness.

994
01:16:49.943 --> 01:16:54.114
A gracious welcome. I must say.
Rise. my dear.

995
01:16:54.323 --> 01:16:57.117
Here are the children
in their. erm...shepherdess outfits.

996
01:16:57.326 --> 01:17:01.496
Well. that's the girls.
The boys... I'm not sure what they are.

997
01:17:01.705 --> 01:17:03.749
But. erm...anyway. you can see.

998
01:17:03.957 --> 01:17:06.126
Oh. keep up. will you?

999
01:17:25.395 --> 01:17:27.397
Who's that?

1000
01:17:27.606 --> 01:17:31.693
- It's a princess.
- A fairy princess.

1001
01:17:33.362 --> 01:17:36.114
It's Evangeline.

1002
01:17:38.867 --> 01:17:42.788
Straight back. Remember your vowels.

1003
01:17:44.122 --> 01:17:49.461
May I present my adopted daughter.
Miss Evangeline Stitch.

1004
01:17:53.507 --> 01:17:57.135
What are we doing milling about
in this dreary vestibule?

1005
01:17:57.344 --> 01:17:59.471
Sherry this instant.

1006
01:17:59.680 --> 01:18:04.184
Might I beg the honour of pouring
the privileged schooners myself?

1007
01:18:05.394 --> 01:18:08.522
Delectable to see you again. madam.

1008
01:18:08.730 --> 01:18:10.899
Blinkin' hell!

1009
01:18:13.110 --> 01:18:15.988
And how nice to see the young people.

1010
01:18:16.196 --> 01:18:20.325
Welcome back. Evangeline.
You look well. Are you well?

1011
01:18:20.534 --> 01:18:23.537
I am most content.

1012
01:18:24.830 --> 01:18:28.625
You must be very happy
to be marrying again.

1013
01:18:29.668 --> 01:18:34.590
Oh. yes. I'm... I'm...
How did you put it? Most content.

1014
01:18:34.798 --> 01:18:37.676
Of course. Good grief.

1015
01:18:39.303 --> 01:18:41.346
I am so glad.

1016
01:18:41.555 --> 01:18:43.724
Evangeline!

1017
01:18:43.932 --> 01:18:46.518
Pray excuse me.

1018
01:18:48.937 --> 01:18:53.192
Are you sure it's Evangeline?
It doesn't look anything like her.

1019
01:18:53.400 --> 01:18:56.278
Nonsense. She's always looked like that.

1020
01:19:28.018 --> 01:19:31.563
What can we do?
There has to be another way.

1021
01:19:31.772 --> 01:19:34.983
- Behave.
- Beehive.

1022
01:19:35.192 --> 01:19:37.069
You must do as you're told.

1023
01:19:37.277 --> 01:19:39.613
- Behave.
- Beehive.

1024
01:19:39.821 --> 01:19:44.785
Lesson number five. Simon.
You must do exactly as you're told.

1025
01:19:53.794 --> 01:19:55.546
Beehive.

1026
01:19:55.754 --> 01:19:57.130
Beehive?

1027
01:19:57.339 --> 01:19:59.049
Please be seated.

1028
01:20:00.843 --> 01:20:03.178
There isn't a beehive. What do you mean?

1029
01:20:06.431 --> 01:20:10.936
Dearly beloved. we are
gathered here together

1030
01:20:11.144 --> 01:20:15.983
in the sight of God
and in the face of this congregation

1031
01:20:16.191 --> 01:20:20.487
to join together this man and this woman

1032
01:20:20.696 --> 01:20:23.657
in holy matrimony.

1033
01:20:23.866 --> 01:20:29.204
which is an honourable estate
instituted of God

1034
01:20:29.413 --> 01:20:32.374
in the time of man's innocence...

1035
01:20:34.877 --> 01:20:37.504
..and commended of St Paul...

1036
01:20:37.713 --> 01:20:41.049
..to be honoured among all men.

1037
01:20:41.258 --> 01:20:42.926
Get off!

1038
01:20:43.135 --> 01:20:45.762
- And is therefore...
- Get off!

1039
01:20:45.971 --> 01:20:49.474
- .. not by any man to be enterprised...
- There's one on you!

1040
01:20:49.683 --> 01:20:55.189
.. nor taken in hand unadvisedly.
lightly. wantonly...

1041
01:20:56.106 --> 01:21:00.611
- There's one on your back!
- ..to satisfy man's carnal lusts...

1042
01:21:00.819 --> 01:21:04.406
It's the flowers on her dress!
They're attracting them!

1043
01:21:04.615 --> 01:21:07.618
- I hate bees. I'm allergic.
- There aren't any bees. you fool!

1044
01:21:07.826 --> 01:21:10.579
No. truly. I swell up.

1045
01:21:10.787 --> 01:21:12.164
They're trying to ruin...

1046
01:21:12.247 --> 01:21:14.708
my lovely wedding. Nasty.
vicious creatures.

1047
01:21:14.917 --> 01:21:17.544
Do something!

1048
01:21:19.254 --> 01:21:22.799
Cedric. look at me. Do you see any bees?

1049
01:21:30.766 --> 01:21:35.562
I said. look at me!
Do you see any bees? Do you?

1050
01:21:35.771 --> 01:21:38.190
- Do you?
- I do.

1051
01:21:38.398 --> 01:21:43.070
It's all right. I've
got the little bugger.

1052
01:21:43.278 --> 01:21:45.822
It's on me!

1053
01:21:46.031 --> 01:21:50.953
Lord love a duck! I'm
so dreadfully sorry!

1054
01:21:53.664 --> 01:21:55.374
No. no. no. no. no...

1055
01:21:58.752 --> 01:22:02.214
Oh. my Lord. Your Higherness!

1056
01:22:31.743 --> 01:22:34.872
- Don't touch the cake!
- Get the tarts!

1057
01:22:35.080 --> 01:22:37.624
- Not me good ones!
- Ow. he hit me!

1058
01:22:38.709 --> 01:22:40.711
Attack!

1059
01:22:42.504 --> 01:22:44.840
Not the cake! Not the cake!

1060
01:22:46.758 --> 01:22:49.511
Right! I'll have the lot of you!

1061
01:22:49.720 --> 01:22:52.389
Simon. bowling practice.

1062
01:23:22.711 --> 01:23:25.297
Evangeline. where are your manners?

1063
01:23:25.506 --> 01:23:27.299
Sod my manners. you old trout.

1064
01:23:27.508 --> 01:23:30.594
This is the first fun I've had in weeks!

1065
01:23:30.802 --> 01:23:35.516
- Oh. Lord.
- Letty. my hair. Where is it?

1066
01:23:35.724 --> 01:23:39.811
"Look at them. the
little. small things."

1067
01:23:40.020 --> 01:23:45.275
That's it! You dreadful. awful.
monstrous creatures!

1068
01:23:45.484 --> 01:23:47.736
Take your hands off my children!

1069
01:23:47.945 --> 01:23:52.282
Cedric. it's over! I won't spend
another minute with this rabble

1070
01:23:52.491 --> 01:23:55.786
and I don't care how much
the old hag is giving you.

1071
01:23:55.994 --> 01:23:58.622
Letty. the lambs!

1072
01:24:02.543 --> 01:24:05.379
- This dress is ruined!
- Absolute carnage!

1073
01:24:05.587 --> 01:24:09.383
A nice choice for a
wife. I must say. Cedric.

1074
01:24:09.591 --> 01:24:12.469
I'm sorry. You gave me no time
to find anyone else.

1075
01:24:12.678 --> 01:24:15.222
As for your children. a lengthy spell...

1076
01:24:15.347 --> 01:24:18.141
in a corrective institution
is long overdue.

1077
01:24:18.350 --> 01:24:20.853
And you. Evangeline. I can see...

1078
01:24:20.936 --> 01:24:24.064
that you are as wild
as the rest of them.

1079
01:24:24.273 --> 01:24:26.817
And proud to be. I love
them. Lady Stitch.

1080
01:24:26.942 --> 01:24:28.485
which is more than you do.

1081
01:24:28.694 --> 01:24:30.571
Insolence!

1082
01:24:30.779 --> 01:24:32.614
I'd leave you here to rot.

1083
01:24:32.739 --> 01:24:35.659
but I gave my word
that I would raise you

1084
01:24:35.868 --> 01:24:39.872
and I never. ever. break my word.
Come away now.

1085
01:25:05.939 --> 01:25:07.774
Wait. Aunt Adelaide! Wait!

1086
01:25:09.151 --> 01:25:11.445
You agreed. You gave your word

1087
01:25:11.653 --> 01:25:14.448
that if our father remarried this month.
you'd support us.

1088
01:25:14.656 --> 01:25:16.325
I did.

1089
01:25:16.533 --> 01:25:19.703
So if he marries today.
you'll have to keep your word.

1090
01:25:19.912 --> 01:25:22.456
- Oh. you're wasting my time!
- No.

1091
01:25:22.664 --> 01:25:25.501
No. No. I'm not.

1092
01:25:26.877 --> 01:25:28.921
- He will marry today.
- What?

1093
01:25:29.129 --> 01:25:30.255
- What?
- What?

1094
01:25:30.464 --> 01:25:31.465
What?

1095
01:25:31.673 --> 01:25:36.220
- Who?
- He'll marry Evangeline.

1096
01:25:45.229 --> 01:25:47.689
Incest?

1097
01:25:47.898 --> 01:25:51.860
No! No. Aunt Adelaide.
Evangeline isn't our sister.

1098
01:25:52.069 --> 01:25:54.613
- Not your sister?
- Of course she's not our sister.

1099
01:25:56.073 --> 01:25:58.200
Well. who is she. then?

1100
01:26:01.703 --> 01:26:04.164
I'm his scullery maid.

1101
01:26:04.373 --> 01:26:05.582
What?

1102
01:26:05.791 --> 01:26:09.127
Evangeline. do you love Papa?

1103
01:26:11.630 --> 01:26:16.134
Of course not. I know my place.
That wouldn't be right. I mean...

1104
01:26:18.053 --> 01:26:19.555
Yes.

1105
01:26:26.270 --> 01:26:28.272
Papa. do you love Evangeline?

1106
01:26:28.480 --> 01:26:30.691
What? That would be totally improper.

1107
01:26:30.899 --> 01:26:33.986
A thing like that
could...could never happen.

1108
01:26:34.111 --> 01:26:35.445
I mean. obviously...

1109
01:26:41.243 --> 01:26:42.953
Yes.

1110
01:26:46.623 --> 01:26:50.127
He's marrying the scullery maid?

1111
01:26:50.335 --> 01:26:51.628
Oh!

1112
01:27:41.845 --> 01:27:43.972
It's snowing!

1113
01:27:44.181 --> 01:27:46.934
Well. I never! Snow!

1114
01:27:47.142 --> 01:27:49.603
Snow in August!

1115
01:28:10.624 --> 01:28:13.252
I take it. then. Mr Brown.

1116
01:28:13.460 --> 01:28:17.047
that the young lady
is not in fact the fruit of your loins?

1117
01:28:17.256 --> 01:28:22.678
Because the Church would have to take
a rather dim view of it if she were.

1118
01:28:22.886 --> 01:28:27.057
No. What happened was my son Simon
is a very clever boy.

1119
01:28:27.266 --> 01:28:28.809
Evangeline...

1120
01:28:29.017 --> 01:28:29.810
for the record.

1121
01:28:29.935 --> 01:28:32.312
whatever I may have
said about stepmothers.

1122
01:28:32.521 --> 01:28:34.481
that whole "evil breed" moment.

1123
01:28:34.690 --> 01:28:38.277
most emphatically does not apply to you.

1124
01:28:42.906 --> 01:28:45.033
This way.

1125
01:28:45.242 --> 01:28:51.206
Jolly good. If I may then invite you all
to join us once more.

1126
01:28:51.415 --> 01:28:52.916
Hallelujah.

1127
01:28:53.125 --> 01:28:57.671
Oh. Nanny McPhee... I'm so nervous.

1128
01:28:57.880 --> 01:29:00.007
Deep breaths.

1129
01:29:01.175 --> 01:29:04.261
I don't look much like a bride. do l?

1130
01:29:05.929 --> 01:29:08.140
You will.

1131
01:30:00.567 --> 01:30:02.986
How's the reading coming along?

1132
01:30:03.195 --> 01:30:05.489
It's much better.

1133
01:30:05.697 --> 01:30:08.784
But I still haven't got to the end
of that story.

1134
01:30:08.992 --> 01:30:13.705
No need. You are the end of the story.

1135
01:30:40.649 --> 01:30:44.570
Dearly beloved. we are gathered together

1136
01:30:44.778 --> 01:30:48.657
to join together this man and this woman

1137
01:30:48.866 --> 01:30:52.077
in holy matrimony.

1138
01:30:57.791 --> 01:31:00.627
Make a loud noise and rejoice

1139
01:31:00.836 --> 01:31:03.046
and sing praise.

1140
01:31:19.438 --> 01:31:20.772
There is something...

1141
01:31:20.856 --> 01:31:23.609
you should understand
about the way I work.

1142
01:31:23.817 --> 01:31:28.864
When you need me but do not want me.
then I must stay.

1143
01:31:29.072 --> 01:31:32.993
When you want me but no longer need me.

1144
01:31:33.202 --> 01:31:35.329
then I have to go.

1145
01:34:02.935 --> 01:34:04.811
Yoo-hoo!

1146
01:34:05.305 --> 01:35:05.253
Tired of searching for subtitles?
Ray generates them instantly: getray.app
